(c) The so-called epistolary use of tlte tenses is the com- monest peculiarity in the use of tenses to be found in the Letters. The writer of the letter imagines himself in the place of the recipient, and therefore uses a tense of past time in speaking of an event which was exactly or approxi- mately contemporaneous with the writing of the letter.
